---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout lang="en" title="Cookie Policy — SyncAgency" description="Cookie Policy for SyncAgency — how we use cookies and how to manage them.">
  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 120px auto; padding: 0 24px 120px;">
    <style>
      .legal-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text-muted, #737373); margin-bottom: 16px; }
      .legal-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px); font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-primary, #F2F2F2); line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .legal-date { font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-text-muted, #737373); margin-bottom: 56px; }
      .legal-intro { font-size: 15px; color: var(--color-text-secondary, #999); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 56px; }
      .legal-section { margin-bottom: 44px; }
      .legal-section-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary, #F2F2F2); margin-bottom: 14px; }
      .legal-section p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--color-text-secondary, #999); line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 12px; }
      .legal-section ul { padding-left: 20px; margin: 8px 0 12px; }
      .legal-section li { font-size: 15px; color: var(--color-text-secondary, #999); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .legal-section strong { color: var(--color-text-primary, #F2F2F2); font-weight: 600; }
      .legal-section a { color: var(--color-primary, #8AA5FF); text-decoration: none; }
      .legal-section a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
      .cookie-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 16px 0; }
      .cookie-table th { padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #999; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
      .cookie-table td { padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 14px; color: #999; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04); vertical-align: top; }
      .cookie-table td:first-child { color: #F2F2F2; font-weight: 500; }
    </style>

    <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="legal-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-date">Last updated: May 10, 2026</p>

    <p class="legal-intro">This Cookie Policy explains how SyncAgency uses cookies and similar technologies when you visit our website. We are committed to a privacy-first approach: we use the minimum number of cookies necessary, and we do not use advertising or cross-site tracking cookies.</p>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2 class="legal-section-title">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your browser when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites function efficiently and to provide useful information to website owners.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2 class="legal-section-title">2. Cookies We Use</h2>
      <p>SyncAgency uses only two categories of cookies:</p>

      <table class="cookie-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Cookie / Technology</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
            <th>Duration</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Session cookie</td>
            <td>Essential</td>
            <td>Maintains your authenticated session in the app</td>
            <td>Session</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Plausible Analytics</td>
            <td>Analytics</td>
            <td>Cookieless, privacy-first analytics — counts page views and events without any personal data or cross-site tracking</td>
            <td>No cookie set</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising cookies, social media tracking pixels, cross-site fingerprinting, or any third-party marketing cookies.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2 class="legal-section-title">3. Essential Cookies</h2>
      <p>Essential cookies are strictly necessary for the website and application to function. They do not collect personal information and cannot be disabled. They include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Authentication session cookies</strong> — required to keep you logged in to the application.</li>
        <li><strong>Security tokens</strong> — protect against cross-site request forgery (CSRF).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2 class="legal-section-title">4. Analytics — Plausible</h2>
      <p>We use <a href="https://plausible.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Plausible Analytics</a>, a privacy-first, open-source analytics tool. Plausible does not use cookies, does not collect personal data, does not track visitors across websites, and is fully GDPR compliant without requiring a cookie banner.</p>
      <p>The data collected by Plausible is anonymized and aggregated: page views, referral sources, browser type, and country-level geography. No individual user is ever identified.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2 class="legal-section-title">5. How to Manage Cookies</h2>
      <p>Because we use only essential cookies and a cookieless analytics tool, there is no cookie consent banner on this site. If you wish to block all cookies, you can configure your browser settings:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
        <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Options → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
        <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
        <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Note: blocking essential cookies may prevent the application from functioning correctly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2 class="legal-section-title">6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Cookie Policy as our use of cookies changes. The current version is always accessible on this page.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2 class="legal-section-title">7. Contact</h2>
      <p>For any questions about our use of cookies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@syncagency.fr">contact@syncagency.fr</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
